   {:e #blake3 "8ae3fb816dc2505042f25eca39b1414b4aa778275f3b942254cdad2bb95dc944" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: C9 principle exists as observations. For 10/10 it must be formalized as invariants with falsification conditions and verification tags.\n\nINV-REFLEXIVE-006: Second-Order Epistemic Closure. STATEMENT: The system MUST apply its own coherence machinery to its own observation layer using the SAME functions it applies to domain observations. The result MUST be surfaceable via a single CLI command, without reading external documents. Every observation retrieval command MUST end with a computed steering question derived from the knowledge graph structure (STEERING_MANIFOLD.md Section 2). FALSIFICATION: Violated if: (a) 10+ observations from 2+ agents, cannot retrieve top 3 convergent findings in one command. (b) Second-order functions differ from first-order functions. (c) braid observe list on 50+ observations fails to show grouped themes. (d) braid observe show on observation with 3+ links fails to display targets. (e) Any observe subcommand output lacks a computed steering question. VERIFICATION: V:PROP, V:TYPE, integration test, E2E.\n\nINV-REFLEXIVE-007: Fixed-Point Property. STATEMENT: Functions for second-order analysis MUST be identical to first-order. No conditional branches for meta vs domain observations. apply(f, apply(f, data)) == apply(f, data). FALSIFICATION: Violated if any C9 function contains a meta-observation special case. VERIFICATION: V:PROP (idempotency proptest), V:TYPE (no meta/domain enum variant).\n\nAPPROACH: (1) Add both invariants to spec/22-reflexive.md with full structure (statement, falsification, verification tags, traces-to, stage). (2) Transact via braid spec create. (3) Add to spec/README.md element counts if needed.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) spec/22-reflexive.md contains INV-REFLEXIVE-006 with 5 falsification conditions including steering question requirement. (B) spec/22-reflexive.md contains INV-REFLEXIVE-007 with fixed-point falsification. (C) Both spec elements exist in store via braid query. FILES: spec/22-reflexive.md. EFFORT: 1h." :op :assert}
